full_summary:
**Request for Proposal (RFP) T8493-220055/A**
==========================================

**Information**
------------

*   **Reference Number**: PW- CAG- 010 -28936
*   **Amendment Number**: 0
*   **Publication Date**: February 2, 2023
*   **Tender Closing Date**: February 16, 2023 at 14:00 (EST)
*   **Tender Status**: Exired

**Notice of Proposed Procurement (NPP)**
-------------------------------------

Public Works and Government Services Canada is inviting suppliers to submit proposals for the acquisition of various aircraft parts.

**Trade Agreement**
------------------

This opportunity is subject to the Canadian Free Trade Agreement (CFTA).

**Section C - Instructions to Proposers**
--------------------------------------

**Trade Agreement Requirements**
--------------------------------

Only suppliers on the permanent list or who can meet the qualification requirements are eligible to bid on this project.

**Selection Criteria**
-------------------

All proposals will be evaluated based on a High Combined Rating of Technical Merit and Price.

**Solicitation Documents**
-------------------------

The solicitation documents will be e-mailed directly to qualified suppliers by the contracting officer. GETS is not responsible for the distribution of these documents.

**Questions**
------------

All inquiries must be submitted to the Contracting Officer listed below.

**Contracting Officer**
----------------------

Edmond Egikian
Acquisitions Branch
Land and Aerospace Equipment Procurement and Support Sector (LAEPSS)
Public Services and Procurement Canada (PSPC) / Government of Canada
11 Laurier Street - PDP III, 8C1, Gatineau, Quebec  K1A 0S5
Phone: 343-572-4437  
Email: edmond.egikian@tpsgc-pwgsc.gc.ca

------------------------------

Oliver Morones
Supply Specialist

11 Laurier Street - PDP III, 7C2, Gatineau, Quebec  K1A 0S5
Phone: 873-455-5233  
Email: oliver.morones@pwgsc.gc.ca

**Delivery Date**
----------------

The delivery date for this project is March 15, 2023. The crown retains the right to negotiate with suppliers on this procurement.
